I achieved a High Distinction in this subject. My approach was to build each task gradually from the ground up, then refine it through multiple iterations and rounds of user acceptance testing to check the accuracy, logic, and reliability of my code. As someone without a traditional programming background, this subject played an important role in developing my confidence in coding and strengthening my approach to structured problem-solving. Much of the learning came not only from getting the code to work, but from repeatedly testing, debugging, and understanding why certain approaches worked better than others.
